race.comment: STAR WHISPERER (9) was lining up for only the second time and appreciated the drop back in distance when he led all the way to record a commanding win over this track and trip last start. Plenty of room for further improvement so expect him to give them a tough lure to catch again. STATE OF GRACE (14) ended a run of four top three finishes with a tiring effort in a Class 2 over 1318m here last time out. Back sharply in distance but this is an easier race so she looms as a serious threat. IMASTATEMENT (3) easily took out a couple of 1100m races before struggling at six furlongs most recently at Cowra. Back in a more suitable contest today - just needs luck from the wide draw to be in the finish. CHARLIE MAGIC (1) started favourite but just failed over this distance at Parkes last start. Is a winner here at the trip and should feature if the wide gate can be overcome. DENMAN FORCE (10) has not appeared since winning on debut at Cowra in July. Market the best guide.
